                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1165a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-02T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1917—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s March 1, 5 p.m. In view of conditions as reported by naval commander
                    at Santiago, recommend that Cuban Government immediately raise blockade and
                    instruct Cuban Consuls to resume issuance of clearances of Santiago.</p>
                <p>Department is communicating with bankers in New York in regard to funds to
                    relieve situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
